100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 29, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Eastern Europe and the Middle East. In the United States, the aftermath of the Scopes Monkey Trial continues to stir debate over education and religion, highlighting the cultural clash of the era. Meanwhile, in Germany, political instability persists as the government struggles to address economic challenges and rising extremist sentiments.
